data.title: Team Members – Makovicka Physical Therapy
data.text:
Betsy Anderson

Pine Lake West

Betsy was born and raised on a farm outside of Wentworth, South Dakota. She received an Athletic Training degree and a Psychology minor from South Dakota State University. She went on to get her Master's Degree in Physical Therapy from the University of South Dakota. Following graduation, she moved to the Lincoln area and she has been part of the Makovicka team since 2010. Betsy treats a variety of diagnoses and specializes in Vestibular/BPPV and women's health. She is certified in RockTape/Kinesiology taping and dry needling. She is a member of APTA and NPTA. Betsy teaches exercise classes at the local YMCA, and her two kids are active in sports. In 2023, Betsy was awarded the very prestigious Inspire Women's Award in the Excellence in Healthcare category. She received the award at a luncheon at the Pinnacle Bank Arena with nearly 800 attendees.

Jeff Arnold

Jeff was born and raised in David City, Nebraska. He moved to Lincoln, Nebraska and received his Bachelor’s degree at Nebraska Wesleyan University, where he was a member of the football team. He then moved to Omaha, Nebraska to attend the University of Nebraska Medical Center. There, he earned his Master and Doctorate degrees in Physical Therapy. Jeff has continued to refine his skills and has been board certified as a Strength and Conditioning Specialist (CSCS) and as an American Board of Physical Therapy Specialties (ABPTS) board certified Orthopedic Clinical Specialist (OCS) . In addition, he is certified as a Sportsmetrics trainer, a program proven to reduce ACL injuries. Jeff is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association, The Nebraska Physical Therapy Association, and The National Strength and Conditioning Association.

Curtis Basnett

University Place

Curtis was born and raised in Ravenna, Nebraska. He received a degree in athletic training from the University of Nebraska-Lincoln. Curtis then moved to Omaha, Nebraska, and attended Creighton University where he earned his Doctorate in Physical Therapy and completed an orthopedic residency through the partnership of Creighton University and Makovicka Physical Therapy. Curtis is a board-certified Orthopedic Clinical Specialist (OCS). As an APTA certified clinical instructor for PT and PTA, he works with students and interns at local schools that are interested in athletic training and physical therapy. In his free time, Curtis enjoys spending time with his wife and three children, helping out on his parent's farm, and creating/building things for his home.

Trevor Bollinger

Plattsmouth

Trevor grew up in Mitchell, South Dakota. He received his Bachelor of Science in Athletic Training from South Dakota State University. He then went on to attend the University of South Dakota where he earned his Doctorate in Physical Therapy. Following graduation, Trevor moved to Papillion with his wife Amy and began practicing as a physical therapist. He is a member of the APTA as well as the neurological chapter of the APTA, and has a special interest in vestibular rehabilitation. In his free time, he enjoys outdoor activities such as hunting, fishing and woodworking as well as spending time with his family.

Landon Booker

70th & L

Landon Booker was born and raised in North Platte, Nebraska. He received a bachelor's degree in Nutrition, Exercise, and Health Science from the University of Nebraska-Lincoln. Landon then attended the University of Nebraska Medical Center receiving his Doctorate of Physical Therapy with high distinction. He is level 1 certified in Functional Dry Needling, and a Certified Strength and Conditioning Specialist through the National Strength and Conditioning Association with experience training both athletes and non-athletes for rehabilitation as well as performance goals. In addition, Landon utilizes blood flow restriction training which is performed with tourniquet pressure monitored with dopler ultrasound during low-load exercise to create the same resistance training adaptations which typically only occur at very high loads/ resistance. This modality is highly suited for rehab to safely and quickly increase strength and muscle size without overly stressing healing tissues. Landon is one of few providers in Lincoln with an isokinetic dynamometer which he uses to help determine readiness of athletes to return to sport following injury especially ACL reconstruction and knee ligament injury.

Chris Cameron

Aksarben, University Place

Chris was born and raised in Davenport, Iowa. He attended St. Ambrose University in Davenport where he earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Psychology, graduating with honors. He then moved to Omaha, Nebraska to attend Creighton University where he graduated with his Doctorate in Physical Therapy. Chris is a board-certified Orthopedic Clinical Specialist (OCS) with extensive experience in treating foot and ankle injuries as well as a Level 2 Functional Dry Needling specialist. He directs Makovicka Physical Therapy’s expanded occupational health program in Lincoln and Omaha and is certified to perform Functional Capacity Evaluations (FCE's). Chris is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association (APTA) and the Nebraska Physical Therapy Association (NPTA). He is currently serving on the Steering Committee for the Better Business Bureau Integrity Award Review Committee in Lincoln. Chris was recently nominated to the Workers Compensation Association of Nebraska Board of Directors and was a 2022 recipient of the National Safety Council Rising Star Award.

Shane Cole

Plattsmouth

Shane is originally from Emmet, NE, attending high school in O'Neill, NE (O'Neill High School). He earned his Bachelor of Science in Exercise Science from the University of Nebraska at Kearney. He earned his Doctorate of Physical Therapy from UNMC. Shane is board-certified clinical orthopaedic specialist, and he is certified in Level 2 Functional Dry Needling through EIM and is an Impact Concussion Trained physical therapist. He is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association--Nebraska Chapter. Shane serves on the Plattsmouth Chamber of Commerce Board of Directors and is involved in many community and civic activities in Cass County. Shane, his wife, Morgan and their son, Lane, currently reside at Beaver Lake. Shane enjoys boating, hunting, fishing, and snow skiing.

Steve Conner

Maple

Steve grew up in Nebraska City, Nebraska and attended Nebraska City High School where he participated in football, basketball and track. Steve went on to attend MidAmerican Nazarene University where he was a member of the track and field team. Steve has a Bachelor of Science in Kinesiology from MidAmerica Nazarene University and a Doctorate of PHysical Therapy from the College of Saint Mary. Steve is a member of APTA and enjoys spending time with his dog, hunting and watching Nebraska athletics outside of work.

Tatem Edwards

Waverly

Tatem is from West Point, Nebraska where she attended West Point Central Catholic High School. She played volleyball, basketball and ran track during her high school years. Tatem went on to attend Nebraska Wesleyan University in Lincoln where she earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Exercise Science. She then attended Des Moines University in Des Moines, Iowa, and earned a Doctorate in Physical Therapy degree. Tatem has a certification in manual physical therapy and is also a member of the APTA and NPTA. In her free time, Tatem enjoys being involved with the Waverly community where she lives with her husband and their two boys.

Angie Evans

Waverly

Angie started with Makovicka Physical Therapy in November of 2006. Before joining MPT, she worked as a physical therapist at St Elizabeth's Regional Medical Center. She obtained her Bachelor of Science Degree from Nebraska Wesleyan University where she played collegiate basketball. Angie continued her education at the University of Nebraska Medical Center and earned a Bachelor of Science Degree in Physical Therapy. Angie enjoys working with all types of orthopedic patients. She has advanced training in manual therapy, PRI techniques, and Functional Dry Needling. She enjoys spending time with her husband, three children and three grandchildren!

Nolan Hanna

Bennington

Nolan was born in Lincoln, Nebraska but later moved to Elkhorn where he attended Elkhorn South High School. He continued his education at the University of Nebraska, Lincoln where he received a Bachelor of Science Degree in Biochemistry. Nolan went on to attend Creighton University where he received his Doctorate in Physical Therapy. In his free time, Nolan enjoys spending time with his wife, Jessica, his family, and his Goldendoodle, Harper. Nolan is also active in sports, specifically basketball and golf. He enjoys working with all patients, but has a special interest in athletes. His favorite aspect of being a physical therapist is building relationships with all of his patients during their journey and getting them back to what they love to do.

Ashton Johnson

119th and Pacific

Ashton was born and raised in Cozad, Nebraska, where she attended Cozad High School and was part of the track team. She then attended the University of Nebraska at Omaha and earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Athletic Training. Ashton earned a Doctorate of Physical Therapy degree from Creighton University. She is married and has one son. Ashton enjoys helping on the family farm, listening to music, cheering on her favorite sports teams, and spending time with her family.

Scott Keenan

West Maple

Scott was born and raised in Omaha, Nebraska, where he graduated from Omaha Roncalli High School. He then attended the University of Nebraska-Omaha where he received his Bachelor’s degree in Exercise Science. Scott was a Graduate Research/Teaching Assistant in the Biomechanics Laboratory at the University of Nebraska-Omaha while completing his Master’s degree. He then went on to attend Creighton University where he received a Doctorate of Physical Therapy. Scott completed an Orthopedic Residency through Creighton University, and is certified as a Strength and Conditioning Specialist. Scott is an American Board of Physical Therapy Specialties (ABPTS) board certified Orthopedic Clinical Specialist (OCS) Scott is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association, the Nebraska Physical Therapy Association and the National Strength and Conditioning Association.

Jedd Lehman

West Omaha/Elkhorn

Jedd was born in North Platte, Nebraska, and grew up in Columbus where he attended Lakeview High School. Jedd played hockey, baseball, and football during his high school years. He attended Wayne State College and went on to Creighton University where he earned his Doctorate in Physical Therapy. Jedd is a board-certified Orthopedic Clinical Specialist (OCS), he is Graston-certified, and Level-1 certified in Dry Needling. He is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association and is the Chair of Makovicka Physical Therapy’s Best Practice Committee. In his free time, Jedd is involved with a local running group and coaches youth soccer, softball, and baseball.

Ashley Loontjer

Gretna

Ashley grew up in Holdrege, Nebraska. She earned her Bachelor's degree from Doane College, Masters in Athletic Training from the University of Nebraska-Omaha and Doctorate in Physical Therapy from Creighton University. She was a member of the basketball team while at Doane College. When Ashley is not in the clinic, she enjoys playing sand volleyball, being outdoors, and spending time with friends and family. Ashley is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association, the Nebraska Physical Therapy Association and the National Athletic Training Association.

Joel Makovicka

Joel was born and raised in Brainard, Nebraska. He attended the University of Nebraska-Lincoln where he not only obtained his Bachelor’s degree but was also a member of the award-winning, three-time, National Championship football teams for the Nebraska Cornhuskers. Upon graduation, Joel moved to Arizona to play in the National Football League (NFL) for the Arizona Cardinals. Following his retirement from the NFL, he coached football at the University of Virginia. There, he learned his true calling was in the field of physical therapy. He graduated with his Doctorate of Physical Therapy from Creighton University and currently focuses his practice on developing physical therapy clinics in Nebraska. Joel is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association and the Nebraska Physical Therapy Association, and he recently served on the Greater Omaha Chamber of Commerce Board of Directors.

Jordan Makovicka

North 90th Street

Jordan was born and raised in Brainard, Nebraska. He attended Creighton University to pursue a baseball career while receiving his Bachelor of Science in Exercise Science. After receiving his bachelor's degree, he continued his education at Creighton where he received his Doctorate of Physical Therapy. Since earning his doctorate, he has pursued advanced training in manual therapy through the North American Institute of Manual Therapy and functional dry needling through KinetaCore. In 2022, Jordan graduated from the University of Nebraska – Omaha with his Master of Business Administration. Jordan is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association and Nebraska Physical Therapy Association.

Dan McCutchen

Dan was born and raised In Tulsa, Oklahoma. He attended college and graduate school at Clarke College in Dubuque, IA where he earned a doctorate in physical therapy. Dan also competed in intercollegiate baseball and tennis while at school. He has since become a board-certified orthopedic clinical specialist (OCS) and received advanced aquatic therapy training. Dan enjoys working with all types of orthopedic patients, especially runners and triathletes. He is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association (APTA) and has served as APTA of Nebraska Executive Board Secretary since 2018. Dan is also an APTA Private Practice Section Payment Policy Committee Member.

Amy Millar

Gretna

Amy is a native of Omaha, Nebraska. She attended Millard North High School, the University of Nebraska at Omaha, and the University of Nebraska Medical Center where she received her Master of Physical Therapy degree. Amy has over 27 years of clinical experience. She enjoys working with all types of orthopedic and vestibular patients. She is a member of the Vestibular Disorders Association (VeDA) and stays up to date on the newest vestibular research. She loves running, quilting, cheering on her daughter in softball, and vacuuming after her Labrador Retriever (Tucker) and Golden Retriever (Moose).

Tammy Phillips

Plattsmouth

Tammy was born in Ogden, Utah. She spent most of her childhood moving around because of her family’s involvement in the Air Force. She attended Alamogoado High School where she participated in cross country and track. After high school, she got her Bachelor's Degree in Sports Administration. She went on and got her Master's and Doctorate in Physical Therapy at Des Moines University. Tammy then furthered her education at North Central University and got her Post Masters in Health Care Administration. She is a member of APTA and NPTA. Tammy is married to Rickie and together they have five kids and ten grandkids. Her hobbies include art, weight training, reading, and horses!

Josh Richling

Josh was born and raised in Beatrice, Nebraska. He received his Bachelor’s degree from the University of Nebraska – Lincoln. He then moved to Omaha to attend Creighton University where he earned a Doctorate in Physical Therapy. Josh has continued to refine his skills and has worked with patients of all ages, with many different diagnoses and functional levels. Josh is also a board-certified Orthopaedic Specialist (OCS), and is certified in Level 1 Functional Dry Needling by Kinetacore. Josh received the Young Alumni Award from the School of Pharmacy and Health Professions at Creighton University. Josh is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association, the Nebraska Physical Therapy Association and a Director Emeritus member of the Alumni Advisory Board of the School of Pharmacy and Health Professions at Creighton University. In his free time, he enjoys spending time with his wife, Angie, and his two children, Anna and Sam.

Gregg Schlueter

Millard

Gregg was born in Lincoln and grew up in Hastings, Nebraska. He attended the University of Nebraska Lincoln and graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Educational and Human Science. He then earned his Doctorate in Physical Therapy from UNMC. Gregg is a board-certified Orthopedic Clinical Specialist (OCS). He was Clinic Director of the Makovicka/Sylliaasen Physical Therapy clinic in Waverly from June 2016 to 2018 as well as Clinic Director of Makovicka Physical Therapy clinics at West O and Aksarben from 2018 to 2019 and 2019 to 2021. Gregg is a Certified Athletic Trainer, and a member of the APTA, Orthopedic section. Gregg is also certified to treat patients with Parkinson's. Gregg is married with three children and enjoys strength training and learning strength coaching techniques in his free time.

Hyun Sik Chang

Bellevue

Hyun Sik was born and raised in Seoul, South Korea. He attended Maur Hill-Mount Academy for high school in Atchison, Kansas. He received his Bachelor of Science in Kinesiology from the University of Illinois. He went on to get a Master's degree in Sports Medicine from Yonsei University in Seoul. Hyun Sik completed his Doctorate in Physical Therapy at the MGH Institute of Health Professions in Boston. Hyun Sik is a Certified Strength & Conditioning Specialist (CSCS) and a member of APTA. He enjoys golf, snowboarding, and taking his dog to the park in his free time.

Kellie Simerly

North 90th Street

Kellie was born and raised in Omaha, Nebraska. She attended Millard West where she participated in track, dance and marching band. Kellie received her Bachelor of Science in Exercise Science from the University of Kansas. While there, she was a member of the KU Marching Jayhawks and Drum Corps International. She went on to get her Doctorate of Physical Therapy from the University of Nebraska Medical Center. Kellie is a member of APTA. Outside of work, she enjoys running half marathons, instructing marching arts and rooting for the Jayhawks.

Mike Spicka

Wahoo

Mike grew up in Wahoo, NE, and is a graduate of Bishop Neumann High School. He went on to the University of Nebraska at Omaha and received his degree in Exercise Science. He completed his Doctorate of Physical Therapy degree from Des Moines University in Des Moines, IA. He enjoys treating patients of all ages and a wide variety of orthopedic conditions. Mike is Level 2 certified for dry needling through EMI and is an American Physical Therapy and Nebraska Physical Therapy Association member. Mike lives in Wahoo, where he enjoys golfing and spending time with his wife and children.

Joel Spiehs

70th & L

Joel was born and raised in Lincoln, Nebraska. He attended Lincoln East High School where he participated in tennis, soccer, baseball, and basketball. Joel earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Nutrition, Exercise Health Science at the University of Nebraska. He attended the University of Mary in Bismarck, North Dakota and received his Doctorate in Physical Therapy. Joel is Level 1 certified in Functional Dry Needling, and he is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association. Joel is an avid Husker fan, and sold Runzas at Nebraska football games for nine years!

Christopher Stull

Shadow Lake

Christopher was born in Kansas City, Kansas, and raised in McCook, Nebraska. He attended the University of Nebraska in Lincoln and received a bachelor's degree in Education and Human Sciences. He then attended Des Moines University where he earned a Doctorate in Physical Therapy. Chris is a board-certified Clinical Orthopaedic Specialist, and is certified in level 2 Dry Needling through EIM. He is also a member of the APTA and the NPTA. Chris has two children with his wife, Jessica.

Kelsey Swan

Papillion

Kelsey grew up in Ralston, Nebraska. She attended Hastings college where she played volleyball and graduated with a bachelor’s degree in biology. Kelsey continued her education at the University of Nebraska Medical Center and earned a Doctorate in Physical Therapy. Kelsey is a board-certified Orthopedic Clinical Specialist (OCS) and Level 2 certified in Dry Needling. Kelsey is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association (ATPA) and the Nebraska Physical Therapy Association (NPTA). She is trained in Herman and Wallace women’s health physical therapy and is the Pelvic Floor coordinator for Makovicka PT. Kelsey has three children with her husband Shawn.

Cory Sylliaasen

Wahoo, Corporate Office

Cory originally hails from the great state of South Dakota. He was raised in Irene and attended Mount Marty College where he received his Bachelor’s degree in Biology/Chemistry. He went on to receive his Doctorate in Physical Therapy from Creighton University. Since then Cory, has practiced outpatient orthopedics, home health, inpatient and skilled nursing physical therapy. He has worked exclusively in the outpatient orthopedic setting since 2001 with an emphasis in sports medicine. Cory has been trained in Postural Restoration and is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association and the Nebraska Physical Therapy Association. He lives in Wahoo, Nebraska and volunteers in numerous community organizations.

Rachel Wallish

Papillion

Rachel was born in Papillion and attended Papillion LaVista High School, where she played volleyball and tennis. She then attended Wesleyan University in Lincoln, earning a Bachelor of Science degree. While at Wesleyan, she was on the volleyball team and a member of the Greenhouse Club. From there Rachel earned a Doctorate of Physical Therapy from the University of Nebraska Medical Center. She is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association, and has certifications including Blood Flow Restriction. She lived and worked in Des Moines, IA, and is excited to return to the Papillion, where she and her husband, Brian, will reside.

Kyle Young

Gretna

Kyle was born and raised in Elkhorn, Nebraska, where he attended Elkhorn South High School and played on the soccer team. He attended the University of Nebraska Lincoln and earned a Bachelor's degree in Business Administration with an emphasis in Management. While a student at the University, he was also a Practice Player for the UNL Husker Women's Soccer Team. He then went on to receive his Doctorate of Physical Therapy from the University of Nebraska Medical Center, and he earned a UNMC Graduation Award for Professionalism. Kyle is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association- Nebraska Chapter.

Casey Buresh

Casey is originally from Fremont, Nebraska, but grew up in LaPorte, Indiana. After graduating high school, he moved to Omaha where he attended Creighton University and received his Bachelor of Science in Exercise Science. From there, he attended Clarkson College and earned his Associate of Physical Therapist Assistant degree. Casey is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association and Nebraska Physical Therapy Association. In his free time, Casey enjoys playing golf and soccer and tries to incorporate these activities into patient care. He is also involved in several philanthropic groups including Mustaches for Kids Omaha and Basset and Beagle Rescue of the Heartland, for which he and his wife serve as a foster home for dogs in need.

Kendy Butterfield

Kendy lives in Plattsmouth, NE., and received a degree in Applied Science from Clarkson College where she was a member of the first accredited graduating class. She is a licensed physical therapist assistant and also works as a PTA in long-term care settings. She is a member of the Accreditation Committee of the APTA and serves as the PTA clinician for the national PTA accreditation program. Kendy has 5 grandchildren that add enjoyment to her life.

Amanda Christensen

Amanda was raised in the town of Brookfield, Missouri, and is one of five siblings. She attended MO Western State University and received her Associate of Applied Science degree as a Physical Therapist Assistant and worked part-time as a PTA for the next two years while finishing her Bachelor of Science in General Psychology. Amanda has an Aquatic Therapy & Rehabilitation certification (ATRIC). Her career has taken her to an additional five states as a contract PTA throughout eight years. This was an experience and opportunity of a lifetime getting to work in so many settings, meeting new friends, and traveling the country. After eight years of traveling, she was ready to settle down and be closer to family and took a job in Lee's Summit, MO at an outpatient clinic. Amanda eventually moved to Omaha to be closer to her fiancé. She married her husband Jay in November of 2022. Outside of work, Amanda enjoys staying active, being involved in the church, serving at Open Door Mission with her husband and colleagues, and spending time with her family and friends. She is excited to be part of the Makovicka PT team and put down roots here in Omaha.

Tori Ellis

Tori is from Greenfield, Indiana. She obtained her Bachelor of Science at Purdue University where she was in the marching band and color guard. She then received her Associate of Science in Physical Therapist Assistant from Clarkson College. Tori is Pelvic Floor Level 1 and 2b trained through the Herman & Wallace Pelvic Rehabilitation Institute. She is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association and the Nebraska DEI Committee. In her free time, she enjoys spending time with her husband and their cat, Winston.

Becca Gillispie

Becca is from Wahoo, Nebraska and attended Bishop Neumann High School. Becca attended Southeast Community College where she earned her Associate of Applied Science for Physical Therapist Associate degree. She loves working with a variety of patients and enjoys making them feel comfortable in an environment that can initially feel intimidating. Becca now lives in Lincoln and enjoys spending time with family, friends. She is a member of the APTA. Outside of work, she enjoys working out and practicing photography. Becca was married in 2019 and has one fur baby, Axle, but would like many more dogs if she could convince her husband!

Didi Gunubu

Odile "Didi" Gunubu was born and raised in Lome, Togo (West Africa). She moved to the United States in 2003 after graduating high school. Didi earned an Associates of Physical Therapist Assistant from Iowa Western in 2019. She advocates for French speaking patients seeking care and enjoys getting to be part of her patients’ rehabilitation journey. Didi is married to her husband, Tofi. Together, they have two kids, Loriane and Aurora. In her free time, she likes to spend time with friends and family and enjoys picnicking at Standing Bear Lake Park.

Melanie Jones

Melanie was born and raised in Columbus, Nebraska, where she attended Columbus High School and played on the softball, basketball, and tennis teams. She then attended Clarkson College in Omaha, where she earned an Associate of Science in Physical Therapist Assistant and a Bachelor of Science in Physical Therapist Assistant. She also minored in Healthcare Business Management. Melanie is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association—Nebraska Chapter. In her spare time, Melanie enjoys being outdoors, staying active, and spending time with family and friends.

Edwin Mendoza

Edwin is a licensed Physical Therapist Assistant. He originally worked as a PT Technician with Makovicka until he graduated from the College of St. Mary's and earned his PTA license. Edwin is well-known throughout the company from floating to each clinic and his positivity and quirkiness he brings every day. When he's not working, he enjoys spending time with his wife Heba, cat Monte, and his huge Filipino family.

Abby Olberding

Makovicka Physical Therapy staff and patients are mourning the loss of one of our team members, Abby Rebecca Olberding, PTA. Abby touched the lives of patients and colleagues in many of our clinics, providing excellent care as a Physical Therapist Assistant, and adding joy to the daily routine. She made friends wherever she went, and her absence creates a void. She will be greatly missed. Our deepest condolences to Abby's family and friends, and all who knew and loved her. Excerpts from Abby's obituary: Abby was born on September 28, 1998, in Omaha, NE, the daughter of Jered and Brenda (Puck) Olberding. She grew up in Carroll, IA and graduated from Carroll High School in 2017 where she participated in track, cross country, band, and softball. Her love of fitness led her to Buena Vista in Storm Lake where she ran track. She graduated in 2020 with a degree in Human Performance. Abby attended Clarkson College and graduated from the Physical Therapist Assistant (PTA) program in the fall of 2022 with an Associate of Science Degree in PTA. She was a member of the National Society of Leadership and Success Honor Society. Abby thrived at her job doing what she loved at Makovicka Physical Therapy. Abby lived life to the fullest. She loved to travel taking memorable trips to Chicago, Minneapolis, Delaware, New York, South Dakota, Maryland, England, Scotland, Florida, Tennessee, Ireland, and Nevada. Abby’s bubbly personality led her to many friendships and a family that adored her. Family and friends describe her as a sweet soul and a ray of sunshine – which is 100% Abby.

Chelsea Popken

Chelsea was born and raised in Scribner, Nebraska. After graduating high school, she went on to receive her Bachelor’s degree in Nutrition, Exercise, and Health Science from the University of Nebraska-Lincoln. Chelsea then moved to Omaha, Nebraska and attended Clarkson College where she earned her Associates of Physical Therapist Assistant Degree. She practiced in central Nebraska for a year and a half before moving back to Omaha, mainly focusing on orthopedics and neuro-muscular re-education. Chelsea has special training LSVT BIG for treating patients with Parkinson's Disease.

Bridgette Powell

Bridgette was born and raised in central Illinois, where she enjoyed playing softball, volleyball, and gymnastics. Bridgette attended Sinclair Community College in Ohio, where she got her Associate’s degree as a Physical Therapy Assistant. She specializes in women’s health and is a member of APTA. Bridgette is married to Kevin, and they have a daughter named Karmyn. In her free time, she likes to crochet and spend time with her family and two dogs.

Jennifer Sabatka

Jennifer was born and raised in Syracuse, Nebraska. After graduating from high school, she attended Briar Cliff University in Sioux City, Iowa, where she was a member of the softball team. She earned her Bachelor of Arts degree in Health, Physical Education, and Recreation as well as a minor in Human Resource Management. Jennifer then moved to Omaha, Nebraska where she attended Methodist College and obtained her Associate of Science in Physical Therapist Assistant degree. Outside of work, Jennifer enjoys spending time with her husband and their two girls.

Stephen Spanel

Stephen grew up in Callaway, Nebraska where he participated in sports and the arts. Stephen went on to attend Midland University where he received a bachelor’s in biology. He later attended Clarkson College where he received his Associate of Science in Physical Therapy Assistant. He is a member of the APTA and enjoys reading, hiking, and rock climbing in his free time.
